        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> , <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0006646> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "<i>De novo</i> (Kennedy pathway) synthesis of phosphatidylethanolamine (PE) involves phosphorylation of ethanolamine (ETA) to phosphoethanolamine (PETA) followed by condensing with cytidine triphosphate (CTP) to form CDP-ethanolamine (CDP-ETA). Diacylglycerol (DAG) and CDP-ETA together then form PE. Alternatively, PE is formed when phosphatidylserine (PS) is decarboxylated by phosphatidylserine decarboxylase proenzyme (PISD) (Henneberry et al. 2002, Vance 1991, Vance 1990)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Synthesis of PE" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Edited: Williams, MG, 2011-08-12" , "Authored: Williams, MG, 2011-09-14" , "Reviewed: Wakelam, Michael, 2012-05-14" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
